:PROFILE [image:cover.jpg]
Ada Lovelace
London, England
Mathematician and writer, 1815 to 1852. Daughter of Lord Byron. Wrote the first \
algorithm in 1843 for Charles Babbage's Analytical Engine. Recognized as the \
first computer programmer more than a century after her death.

:POLL
